verbose_text: Interestingly, the elevated spontaneous WDR activity observed in neuropathic conditions was not inhibited by pregabalin (baseline : 27.6 +/- 4.94 spikes/s, pregabalin : 27.8 +/- 5.77 spikes/s; paired t-test, P = 0.951); spontaneous firing in sham rats was also unaffected (baseline : 6.09 +/- 1.15 spikes/s, pregabalin : 3.86 +/- 1.27 spikes/s; paired t-test, P = 0.089).
evidence: WDR activity observed in neuropathic conditions was not inhibited by pregabalin
